DistTypeName: Unknown
Description: Unknown disturbance type.

DistTypeName: Wildfire
Description: Wildfire causing stand mortality.

DistTypeName: Insect disturbance
Description: Insect infestations resulting in stand mortality.

DistTypeName: Clear-cut with slash-burn
Description: Applies to areas that were clearcut and slash–burned in the same year.  It is assumed that this will remain as "forestry" land use.

DistTypeName: Clearcut harvesting with salvage
Description: Applies to areas where clearcut logging occurs. Salvage moves 50% of stem snags to the forest products sector.

DistTypeName: Fire with salvage logging
Description: Applies to areas where a non stand–replacing fire occurred followed by salvage logging.  This sequence of events is assumed to have occurred in the same year.  Also, it is assumed that this will remain as "forestry" land use.

DistTypeName: Insect disturbance with salvage logging
Description: Applies to areas where an insect infestation has/may occur and is subsequently salvage logged.  This sequence of events is assumed to have occurred in the same year.  Also, it is assumed that this will remain as "forestry" land use.

DistTypeName: Deforestation
Description: The conversion of forested land to a nonforest land use, for example, forest to agricultural land.

DistTypeName: Afforestation
Description: The conversion of land that has been nonforest for at least 50 years to forested land.

DistTypeName: Natural nonforest rehabilitation
Description: Natural conversion of land from nonforest to forest. This will not cause immediate C stock changes.

DistTypeName: Partial cutting
Description: Partial cutting removes 50% of the merchantable biomass from a stand.

DistTypeName: Natural succession
Description: For users who explicitly model natural succession in stands as events. No stock changes are associatied with this disturbance type.
